<P>
   REFLECT-AD-COLUMN (Undated) _ A high-profile entrant in one of
the most crowded categories of e-commerce is hoping to gain a
competitive edge with a campaign that plays up what are deemed to
be its beautiful points of differentiation. By Stuart Elliott.
</P>
<P>
   E-COMMERCE-COLUMN (Undated) _ E-commerce companies have long
coveted the back-end business structures of catalog companies. Now
they've got their eyes on the front end as well. The number of pure
plays that are rolling out their own catalog operations is growing
briskly, as they seek new ways to market themselves in a
cost-effective manner, and generate more revenue. By Bob Tedeschi.
</P>
<P>
   (ART ADV: Photo [NYT5) has been sent to NYT photo clients.)
