O'BANNONS HEDqjk2  I S PAST CANADA 
(For use by NYTimes News Service clients) 
By SEAN KEARNS  
 Long Beach Press-Telegram  
<TEXT>
<P>
   LONG BEACH, Calif. _ Maybe the O'Bannon house could become its
own country. Possibly get a flag and compose an anthem of some
kind.
</P>
<P>
   It wasn't the Olympic games, but Ed and Charles O'Bannon, along
with Baron Davis and the LA Pros, defeated the Steve Nash-led
Canadian Olympic team 113-99 in the Summer Pro League at the
Pryamid.
</P>
<P>
   ``I wish I could play in the Olympics,'' said Ed O'Bannon, who
led LA Pros with 21 points. ``I think we wanted to come out and
play hard. They're a nation team and Olympic team.''
</P>
<P>
   Ed O'Bannon played last season in Greece and Argentina and
worked out on his own in preparation for the Summer League.
</P>
<P>
   The LA Pros hadn't practiced together for the summer league;
they basically threw the ball out and played Sunday at the Pyramid.
</P>
<P>
   Charles O'Bannon had 16 points and Davis, who flew to the rim on
a number of alley-oop attempts and some completions, finished with
21.
</P>
<P>
   Add Canada: The Canadian Olympic team is at the Summer Pro
League for four games in five days in preparation for Sydney in
September.
</P>
<P>
   ``We want to play against the best competition we can play
against,'' said Canada coach Jay Triano in an interview before the
game. ``We felt we needed to go against the best players available.
We knew we could play a lot of games in a short period of time.''
</P>
<P>
   Canada qualified for the Olympics in a tournament in San Juan,
Puerto Rico. The team faces a tough bracket in the Olympics with
host Australia, Russia, Yugoslavia, Spain and Angola. Triano said
Canada would be considered the fifth seed out of the six teams.
</P>
<P>
   Not playing for Canada is Laker Rick Fox and Jamaal Magloire,
the first-round pick of the Charlotte Hornets. But the team does
have Dallas Mavericks point guard Nash.
</P>
<P>
   ``We have to be prepared as a team to be ready for the
Olympics,'' Nash said in a previous interview.
</P>
<P>
   Clippers in action: Without any of their top draft picks or
new &LR; T &Cx1f; %M%Q% &QC; 9M1''!
</P>
</TEXT>
