 BC- CAKE 
 &HT;    TEACHER'S TRANSFER ANGERS MESA PARENTS(a) 
 &HT;    (For use by N.Y. Times News Service clients)(a) 
 &HT;    By REPORTER NAME(a) 
 &HT;    c.2000 The Arizona Republic(a) 
<TEXT>
<P>
   Everyone laughed when Mesa first-grade teacher David Cummings
jokingly smashed a piece of cake into the principal's face at the
end-of-the-year faculty party.
</P>
<P>
   No one's laughing now.
</P>
<P>
   Pomeroy Elementary School Principal Pat Kordelski, who witnesses
said seemed to be enjoying Cummings' mock threat until he actually
lobbed it, complained to Mesa Unified School District officials.
</P>
<P>
   The longtime teacher's forced transfer to another school has
provoked an angry uprising among parents who think Cummings has
been punished unfairly for the May19 gag {ndash} and that Kordelski
is too tough for their children.
</P>
<P>
   ``She wanted to have him fired. Over a piece of cake,'' parent
Petty Denisuk said. ``It's just blown out of proportion.''
</P>
<P>
   Dozens of parents banded together to support Cummings, and
presented the district with two petitions: one to reinstate
Cummings at Pomeroy and the other to have Kordelski transferred.
</P>
<P>
   They passed out hundreds of fliers and put up yard signs reading
``Save Our School'' and ``We Support Mr. C.''
</P>
<P>
   Now, afdh+
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
<TRAILER>
NYT-07-10-00 0800EDT &QL; 
</TRAILER>
