<P>
   HOUSING (San Jose, Calif.) {ndash} Envy tinged the voice of
Maricopa County (Ariz.) Supervisor Mary Rose Wilcox last week as
she gazed around a modern, sunlit building here.
``(beginitalic)This(enditalic) is a homeless shelter?'' she
murmured as fellow Supervisor Jan Brewer stood nearby, shaking her
head in disbelief at the Montgomery Street Inn, a shelter for
homeless men. The spacious central dining hall features skylights
in a high ceiling. Men live in spotlessly clean, curtained
cubicles. Restrooms are immaculate. ``How did you get the capital
to build this?'' asked Wilcox, who with Brewer and other
