cable channel, the last letter in hype) and blanket advertising.
</P>
<P>
   Studios usually spend one and a half times the production budget
of a movie on publicity, and with the average summer picture
costing close $70,000,000, that's real money.
</P>
<P>
   Since 1975, the year in which ``Jaws'' ate the box office, the
