<SLUG> BC-R-THEATER-SUPERSTITION-REVIEW-NYT </SLUG>
<HEADLINE>
OUT SPOTS, CATS AND BAD LINES 
</HEADLINE>
   (The Week in Review)  
 By JESSE McKINLEY   
 c.2000 N.Y. Times News Service    
<TEXT>
<P>
   Short of dinner theater or being cast in a musical about tooth
decay, there are few terrors that hold more sway over theater folk
than the curse of ``Macbeth.'' Legend has it that the hex dates
from the first production in 1606, when the actor playing Lady
Macbeth died backstage, cursing the play.
</P>
