   TRAVEL (``t' category)
</P>
<P>
   TOURING-DAWN (Undated) _ Long ago I learned that dawn is,
without a doubt, the most rewarding time of day for sightseeing. In
the hours just after dawn, fruit and vegetable markets spring to
life in market squares and plazas. Old women dressed in black
shuffle out of bakeries. Life is gbeginning to stir. By JOHN FLINN.
</P>
