</P>
<P>
   OSTEOPOROSIS-DRUGS _ These five drugs help prevent bone loss and
rebuild osteoporatic bones. (Guthrie, Atlanta
Journal-Constitution). 9.
</P>
<P>
   SAVANNAH-MUSEUM _ ``It's a great `Midnight' story.'' That's how
Savannah museum director Diane Lesko characterizes the war of wills
that's been going on for 18 months between arts advocates pushing a
glassy contemporary museum expansion for the historic district and
the preservationists on the city's historic review board, who keep
sending the modern building and it's Boston-based architect back to
the drawing board. The next big vote is slated for Wednesday July
12. (Sabulis, Atlanta Journal-Constitution).
</P>
<P>
   CONSUMERQ&AMP;A _ AUSTIN, Texas _ Consumer Q&AMP;A. (Greig, Austin
American-Statesman) (l, a). MOVED.
</P>
<P>
   NEWS FOR KIDS
</P>
<P>
   NFK-NEWSFLASH _ Three or four briefs of world and national news,
written for kids to understand. (Atlanta Journal-Constitution)
MOVED.
</P>
<P>
   NFK-FEATURE-ALLSTAR_ A feature about a celebrity kid, kid's
event, or big news story explained for kids, for papers' kids or
family pages. (Atlanta Journal-Constitution) MOVED.
</P>
<P>
   ENTERTAINMENT/ARTS
</P>
<P>
   BIGBROTHER _ Week One of Big Brother is done _ and is the show
as well? Ratings have slid for each successive broadcast and some
critics, including the NYT, have written it off. A look at how the
show has done overall, the local numbers, the website hits and what
CBS might do to try to help Big Brother.. survive? (Jubera, Atlanta
Journal-Constitution). 16.
</P>
<P>
   HOLLOWAY-TVCOLUMN _ Observations on the television industry from
a leading commentator. This week: New fall season shows airing
opposite ``Who Wants to be a Millionaire?'' (Holloway, Austin
American-Statesman) MOVED.
</P>
<P>
   STRUGGLING-MUSICIAN _ More than a decade ago, Austin resident
Derek Geary stood at the edge of fame and fortune. He was 18 and
had just been drafted by the Boston Bruins. Then he suddenly gave
it all up because of a greater love for something else _ the piano.
Now, Geary is a struggling musician working at Twin Liquors by day
and trying to make something of himself in his free time. He has a
new CD and a lot to say about the Austin music scene. He is a man
haunted by his past as he looks toward his future. (Barchas, Austin
American-Statesman). 45.
</P>
<P>
   NEWSSTAND _ Periodicals on the newsstands this week. (O'Briant,
Atlanta Journal-Constitution)
</P>
