<P>
   PRACTICAL-MAN _ The practical man got soaked last week. At the
movies. He thought he was going to see The Perfect Storm _ a
tough-minded sea-going tragedy based on a gripping book of the same
name. But it
</P>
<P>
   turned out to be The Perfect Corn _ a sappy sea-going snoozer
based on a dozen other cheesy melodramas he's moped through in his
moviegoing life. (Practical Man, Palm Beach Post). 50 inches.
</P>
<P>
   LILLYLINENS _ It's a hot one in Palm Beach, but Lilly Pulitzer
Rousseau is keeping cool at home, her island retreat with the thick
tropical jungle, the one she playfully calls ``the Palm Beach
Taj.'' There's going to be a party on this night to celebrate some
family
</P>
<P>
   birthdays, and she plans to be ready for a summery fiesta, right
down to the margarita machine. (Graulich, Palm Beach Post)
</P>
<P>
   CLERMONT _ CLERMONT _ If you are looking for a pleasant,
inexpensive, fun-Disneyfied weekend getaway, within three hours'
drive of Palm Beach
</P>
<P>
   County, then take the high ground. Here, within a few minutes'
drive of each other, are three inexpensive
</P>
<P>
   tourist attractions, an atmospheric old downtown, and a
profusion of more than 1,400 blue lakes where you can bicycle and
picnic atop the rolling hills of the Florida Ridge. But you better
come quick: Lake County is growing by leaps and bounds, becoming a
bedroom community for burgeoning Orlando. New housing divisions are
being sculpted in fanciful swirls over hills that once were clad
with orange groves as far as the eye can see.(Browning, Palm Beach
Post). 100 inches.
</P>
<P>
   AIRFARES _ So I'm sitting at lunch on a recent Wednesday, and I
say to my co-workers, ``Guess what I'm doing this weekend?'' And
they can't possibly guess because it's just so spontaneous. And it
seems like
</P>
<P>
   something I couldn't possibly afford. I'm flying to Boston with
just 60 hours notice! Every Wednesday, I get e-mails from a handful
of airlines: Delta, USAirways, Continental and American. And they
all tell me about last-minute ``e-saver'' sales on their Saturday
flights _ one week, I can fly from West Palm Beach to Boston and
back for $159. (If I were to buy a regular round-trip ticket just
three days in advance, it would likely cost more than $400.)
(Flannery, Palm Beach Post). 35 inches.
</P>
<P>
   EPISCOPAL-GAYS _ Episcopalians, meeting this week in Denver, are
expected to once again tackle the issue of the rights of Gays
within the denomination. Church members are also expected to debate
and vote on a number of other issues that may have more resonance
on the local level than the sometimes fuzzy issue of homosexuality.
Delegates plan to break into small groups to discuss racism,
violence, ethnic diversity, liturgy and end-of-life issues. The
meeting ends on Thursday. (GWhite, Atlanta Journal-Constitution).
20.
</P>
<P>
   ALZHEIMER'S _ WASHINGTON _ A failing memory may not be a symptom
of Alzheimer's disease but of a treatable and reversible condition,
Danish scientists report here Monday at the Alzheimer's conference.
(Nesmith, Cox News Service). 20.
</P>
<P>
   Moving on the NYT wire in the (w) Washington and (l) lifestyle
categories.
</P>
<P>
   BIGBUGS _ A Chinese praying mantis more than 21 feet long
extending its sharp forearms to catch prey is making its home at
the Boonshoft Museum of Discovery through Sept. 10. The ``What Bugs
Us'' exhibit from Kokoro Ltd. in Tokyo, Japan, includes robotic
insects more than 600 times life size and a roomful of live
insects, including the walking stick and hissing cockroaches, plus
an array of close-up bug pictures accompanied by educational
information. (Dayton Daily News) WITH PHOTOS
</P>
<P>
   OSTEOPOROSIS _ The best predictor of osteoporosis, the
bone-thinning disease that afflicts millions of women and some men,
is heredity. Talking to a Decatur, Ga., woman and her mother who
are a good example and to doctors about new research into
prevention, treatment. (Guthrie, Atlanta Journal-Constitution). 30.
WITH GRAPHIC, PHOTOS.
</P>
<P>
   WITH
</P>
<P>
   OSTEOPOROSIS-DRUGS _ These five drugs help prevent bone loss and
rebuild osteoporatic bones. (Guthrie, Atlanta
Journal-Constitution). 9.
</P>
<P>
   SAVANNAH-MUSEUM _ ``It's a great `Midnight' story.'' That's how
Savannah museum director Diane Lesko characterizes the war of wills
