   WASHINGTON NEWS (``w'' category)
</P>
<P>
   MISSILE-DEFENSE (Washington) _ Supporters of the proposed
National Missile Defense program argue that the system's
embarrassing test failure last weekend wasn't caused by any
fundamental flaw in the weapon. The Pentagon says the test flopped
because the booster rocket _ a Minuteman missile refurbished by
Lockheed Martin Corp. _ failed to jettison its cargo, a ``kill
vehicle'' that was to have homed in on a dummy warhead in outer
space. Sen. John Kyl, R-Ariz., called the test ``disappointing,''
but added that ``the primary failure had to do with a technology
that is not a new technology, that is, separating a booster from
its payload. There is nothing about this latest test that would be
definitive about not proceeding with National Missile Defense.'' By
ERIC ROSENBERG.
</P>
<P>
   EXECUTION-DELAYED (Washington) _ The White House has issued a
stay of execution for Raul Garza, the convict's lawyer says. The
stay had been widely expected. DEBORAH TEDFORD.
</P>
