frisks a black man in Camden during a ride-along with state
troopers in 1996. The photo, which has been subpoenaed by two
troopers who have filed a discrimination suit against the state,
was obtained by The Associated Press and distributed over the
weekend to the news media. The symbolism of the photo, and the
facts of the frisking _ the man was stopped for ``suspicious
activity'' but never found to be violating the law _ have stirred
criticism about Whitman's response to discrimination complaints
against troopers and has renewed questions about her sensitivity to
inner-city residents. By David Kocieniewski.
