sports league has tried to control the use of the material
journalists' gather at sporting events. It underscores a growing
determination of the owners of entertainment properties to control
their products and any profits that come from them. The Times sold
a package of five photographs of Knick games for $900 on its online
store. By Felicity Barringer.
