<P>
   ARLINGTON, Texas _ The name Zen means ``to meditate
peacefully,'' or seeking the truth by meditation, as a means of
achieving a harmonious relationship between nature and human
beings. It was introduced from China to Japan, and spread along
with Buddhism, according to Zen Master Miao Tien, in an article
titled ``The General Concept of Zen.'' In America, it has been used
by Christians, Jews and others to achieve harmony and balance in a
chaotic world. By JAIME JORDAN. Story has moved in ``l'' lifestyle
category. &QL; 
