<P>
   BUCHANAN _ He's just another Texan with an opinion, but five
books and almost 30 years after he began studying the presidency,
Bruce Buchanan's thoughts now are sought - on a daily basis - from
around the world as the George W. Bush campaign evolves. In his
fourth floor office at Burdine Hall at the University of Texas,
Buchanan has become a high-profile member of the corps of
Austinites whose lives are now intertwined with the Bush race for
the White House. (Austin American-Statesman)
