   SAVANNAH-MUSEUM _ ``It's a great `Midnight' story.'' That's how
Savannah museum director Diane Lesko characterizes the war of wills
that's been going on for 18 months between arts advocates pushing a
glassy contemporary museum expansion for the historic district and
the preservationists on the city's historic review board, who keep
sending the modern building and it's Boston-based architect back to
the drawing board. The next big vote is slated for Wednesday July
12. (Sabulis, Atlanta Journal-Constitution).
