</P>
<P>
   &UR; NATIONAL (a) &LR;
</P>
<P>
   BIGDIG-SLATER (Washington) _ Meeting with Paul Cellucci for the
first time since releasing a humiliating federal audit of the ``Big
Dig,'' US Transportation Secretary Rodney E. Slater reassures the
Massachusetts governor about his handling of the highway budget
crisis, indicating his agency would approve the state's new
financing plan by the end of this month. By Anne E. Kornblut. 1000
words.
</P>
<P>
   HOCKEY-MANSLAUGHTER (Boston) _ Two killings, two totally
different charges. When baby Matthew Eappen was shaken to death,
Louise Woodward was charged with first-degree murder, a stiff
charge many thought excessive -- including the judge. Now, under
new leadership, the same district attorney's office seeks a
manslaughter conviction in the case of a hockey dad beaten to death
outside a rink. By Sacha Pfeiffer. 900 words.
</P>
<P>
   &UR; FINANCIAL (f) &LR;
