<P>
   K2DESIGN-AD-COLUMN (New York) _ A leading agency in the
interactive services field is branching out with its first
acquisition, entering the potentially lucrative but risky realm of
wireless services. K2 Design Inc. in New York, which handles
Internet marketing for advertisers like Hewlett-Packard, IBM,
Philips and Standard &AMP; Poor's, plans to announce on Tuesday that it
will join with a venture capital partnership to indirectly acquire
for $14.8 million in stock and cash a majority interest in
SilverCube Inc. A wireless professional services company,
Silvercube works for marketers like General Motors and Edmunds, a
clearing house for automotive data. By Stuart Elliott.
</P>
<P>
   (Will move by 9 p.m.)
</P>
<P>
   TIMES-EARNINGS (New York) _ The New York Times Co. will report
second-quarter earnings later Monday. The consensus forecast is 56
cents a share. By Felicity Barringer.
</P>
<P>
   (Will move by 8:30 p.m.)
</P>
<P>
   EADS-STOCK (Frankfurt, Germany) _ Shares of the newly formed
European aerospace giant EADS _ a combination of three Airbus
partners, Dasa of Germany, Casa of Spain and Aerospatiale of France
_ have an unspectacular debut in Paris, Frankfurt and Madrid. By
Edmund L. Andrews.
</P>
<P>
   (Will move by 9 p.m.)
</P>
<P>
   TOYSMART-PRIVACY (Undated) _ The Federal Trade Commission sues
to stop Toysmart.com's effort to sell thousands of customer names
and data despite an earlier pledge by the company, now in
bankruptcy protection, never to do so. By Matt Richtel.
</P>
<P>
   (Will move by 8 p.m.)
