r l BC-LEAH-PERSONALS-SFCHRO     07-10 0412
</HEADER>
<BODY>
<SLUG> BC-LEAH-PERSONALS-SFCHRON </SLUG>
  
 
 PERSONALS: `Survivor' Versus the Nation 
<TEXT>
<P>
   &UR; (Eds: This story also moved in the ``a'' national news file.) &QL;  &LR; 
 &UR; By LEAH GARCHIK &QC;  &LR; 
 &UR; c.2000, San Francisco Chronicle &LR;  &QC; 
 &QL; 
_ ``The Early Show'' has been devoting two full segments every
Thursday morning to discussions of ``Survivor,'' notes the Nation,
which also reports that local TV stations give the presidential
race an average of 39 seconds a night.
</P>
<P>
   The magazine's suggestion: ``Put Gore and Bush on a desert
island and call the show `Political Survival.' In November, viewers
vote either of them off. That should put the election back on the
morning and nightly news.''
</P>
<P>
   _ George magazine, ever sprightlier, gives  &UR; Al Gore  &LR; its Suck-Up
of the Month award, for ``as usual . . . trying too hard.''
</P>
<P>
   Apparently feeling inadequate because of  &UR; George W. Bush &LR; 's
strengths among Latinos _ the Republican speaks some Spanish and
has a Latino sister-in-law _ Gore told Latino leaders in Chicago:
``My grandson was born on the Fourth of July. If I have another
child, I hope he's born on Cinco de Mayo.''
</P>
<P>
   George W. called the comment ``totally pathetic.''
</P>
<P>
   &QL; 
 &UR; FLASH &LR;
</P>
<P>
   _  &UR; Prince William &LR; 's personal coat of arms, revealed Sunday,
July 9, on the occasion of his 18th birthday, includes an image of
a red scallop shell, in homage to his mother. The shell, placed
there at the request of the prince, has appeared on the Spencer
crest since the 16th century.
</P>
<P>
   _ Attention Harrods shoppers: &UR; Mohamed al-Fayed &LR;  said on Sunday
that  &UR; Prince Philip &LR;  would not be welcome in his store. This was in
response to the prince's withdrawing of the royal warrant from
Harrods, which most royal watchers figure was in response to
Fayed's charging the prince with plotting the car crash that killed
 &UR; Princess Diana  &LR; and  &UR; Dodi Fayed &LR; .
</P>
<P>
   _ A Qtopics survey of 800 teenagers found that 64 percent of
14-year-old girls curious about  &UR; Britney Spears &LR;  would ask her if
she has had breast implants.
</P>
<P>
   &QL; 
 &UR; WHO SAID WHAT &LR;
</P>
<P>
   ``Q: What's the strangest habit you have when you're working on
a book? &QL; 
A: Whatever strange habits I have are those that relate to a
particular book. For example, while working on my novel, `Poison,'
which included a lot of bloodletting, I became a compulsive blood
donor.''
</P>
