child!" when the doctor speaks with authority, professionalism and
calmness. The patients of Dr. Valerie Asher, an ear, nose and throat
specialist in a group practice in Silver Spring, Md., for example,
say she exudes a confidence that belies her age, 39. "It helps that
I'm tall and I've been a bossy person my whole life," says Asher,
examining a patient. (Marty Katz/The New York Times) *LITE
